# Web design system — "Hearth" (`apps/web`)

Source design: Claude Design handoff "Hearth UX Plan" (warm, friendly, mobile-first household finance). The prototype is English LTR; the app is **Hebrew RTL** — mirror layouts, keep the visual language.

## Visual language

- **Typography:** single family for everything — `"Plus Jakarta Sans", "Heebo", system-ui, sans-serif` (Plus Jakarta Sans has no Hebrew glyphs; Heebo renders the Hebrew). Hierarchy comes from weight, not family: 800 page titles and amounts, 700 headings/row titles, 600 labels and secondary text, 400–500 body.
- **Color system (OKLCH, via CSS variables in `apps/web/src/index.css`):**
  - `background` warm cream `oklch(96% 0.02 80)`; `card` near-white `oklch(99% 0.008 80)`; `muted` `oklch(93% 0.025 75)`; `border` `oklch(89% 0.02 70)`.
  - `foreground` warm ink `oklch(27% 0.03 50)`; `muted-foreground` `oklch(52% 0.02 55)`.
  - **`primary` ember terracotta `oklch(62% 0.16 38)`** — active nav, primary CTAs, main progress. Soft companion `primary-soft` bg `oklch(93% 0.03 40)` with `primary-strong` text `oklch(50% 0.15 38)` for chips/banners.
  - Money/status: `negative`/`destructive` red `oklch(58% 0.18 25)` (expenses, over budget, quick-add FAB); `positive` green `oklch(56% 0.09 155)` + `positive-soft` `oklch(93% 0.04 155)` (income, on-track); `warning` amber `oklch(80% 0.12 82)`; `info` blue `oklch(60% 0.12 250)`; `violet` `oklch(55% 0.13 320)` (transfers). These five also serve as category dot colors.
- **Surfaces & depth:** cards are `bg-card` with a **1px `border`** — prefer visible borders over shadows. Soft *colored* shadows only for the hero card and FAB (e.g. `shadow-[0_14px_30px] shadow-primary/30`).
- **Geometry:** moderate rounding — cards/containers `rounded-card` (~18–22px), rows/controls `rounded-control` (~12–14px), chips/pills/segmented controls fully rounded (`rounded-full`).
- **Signature components:** gradient net-worth hero card (`primary` → darker terracotta); grouped list cards (rows inside one rounded bordered card, separated by 1px inner borders); segmented control (muted track, white active segment); progress rings (SVG stroke-dasharray) and thin rounded progress bars; dashed-border upload zone; step progress (thin segment bars); bulk-select bar on `primary-soft`.
- **Icons:** `lucide-react` outlined icons, stroke `1.5–2`; active bottom-tab icons switch to `primary` color (no circular backgrounds).
- **Motion:** subtle `0.3s ease-in-out` transitions on hover/active; no large movement.
- **Tokens only:** use semantic Tailwind colors from the CSS variables (`bg-card`, `text-muted-foreground`, `bg-primary/10`, …). No ad-hoc hex/OKLCH in components except rare charts; document exceptions.

## Dark mode

- `html.dark` follows OS preference (`theme.ts` + inline script in `index.html`). Dark tokens are warm-dark (same hues, low lightness). Style with semantic tokens so both modes work; check contrast in both.

## Hebrew and RTL

- Document root: **`lang="he"`**, **`dir="rtl"`** (see `index.html`).
- **User-facing strings:** Hebrew by default, including validation copy in shared Zod schemas consumed by the web app.
- **Layout:** prefer **logical** Tailwind utilities — `ms`/`me`, `ps`/`pe`, `text-start`/`text-end`, `rounded-s`/`rounded-e`, `start-`/`end-` insets — never physical `ml`/`mr`/`left`/`right` unless intentionally LTR (e.g. monospace numbers/URLs).
- **Icons:** chevrons, arrows, and "back" cues must mirror in RTL (`rtl:scale-x-[-1]` or logical icon choice).
- **Numbers and money:** format with shared helpers (`Intl` locale `he-IL`, currency from the household, default ILS). Amounts stay as decimal strings until display; never floats for persisted money. Expenses render in `negative`, income in `positive`.

## Navigation model

- **Mobile (<lg):** bottom tab bar — בית, חשבונות, תקציבים, ייבוא, עוד — plus a quick-add FAB (`negative` red, `rounded-control`) floating above it.
- **Desktop (≥lg):** right-side sidebar (RTL start side) with household name header and rows for בית, חשבונות, תקציבים, ייבוא, הוראות קבע, משק בית; active row = `primary-soft` bg + `primary-strong` text.

## Layout and a11y

- Mobile-first; content column max ~`max-w-2xl` on module pages, wider for desktop dashboards.
- Semantic HTML, labels on controls, visible focus rings (`ring` = primary); adequate touch targets (≥40px); WCAG AA contrast for terracotta on cream in both modes.

